This paper deals with reasoning in Fuzzy Description Logics (FDLs), which are logic-based formalisms used to represent and reason with vague or imprecise knowledge. This topic is closely related to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic (cs.LO), machine learning (cs.LG), knowledge representation and reasoning (cs.DL), and fuzzy logic (cs.FL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
